  "riddle": "1. Seek the neighborhood that preserves the essence of Omaha’s past — in which year was its gateway built?\n\n2. A significant page exists where the many faces of preserved history are cataloged — how many different languages can you find represented at the top?\n\n3. What legislative body bestowed upon the nation a law dedicated to safeguarding its historic treasures?\n\n4. This grand event showcased the wonders of the West — from which coordinates can you plot its historic site?\n\n5. In the vicinity of this exposition's grounds, how many places of worship can one find? \n\n6. Between the bustling cities of Dallas and Omaha, what is the distance that connects their hearts by road?\n\n7. From the length you discovered in the previous riddle, count how many 1s appear when transformed into the language of binary.\n\n8. Uncover the legacy of the team whose ballparks have worn the test of time — what names and years can you uncover?\n\n9. Within the title of this storied franchise, how many vowels can be found dancing in its name?\n\n10. Investigate the squared edges of baseball’s home base — what dimensions are given for its shape and thickness?\n\n11. On the mound stands a legend with a career measure — what was his earned run average, a testament to his skill?\n\n12. Finally, compute the single digit by finding the digital root of the sum from clues 1, 2, 9, and 11, expressed as: digital_root(clue 1 + clue 2 + clue 9 + clue 11). What is this final value?",
